reviews.review: It closes all the holes, but it seemed choppy.   Too slow in the beginning, to fast at the end, and too many seeds for where Disney wants to off-spin to next movies, etc.  It does not live up to what The Force Awakens promised.

This movie is wonderful I grew up on Star Wars, They've been a part of who I am for so long that I used to think my memories of watching over my actual memories to see this last episode spectacular that's it it's a spectacular movie it's fine don't overthink it just enjoy it they killed it

It definitely cleaned up the mess from the last Jed and I liked some of the themes of this movie. When it came to starwars force and cannon lore it definitely fails! To the causal fan this will be a good flick. To the starwars superfan this movie has ridiculous use of the force which make no sense when taking all 9 movies into account as a whole.
It was a great movie and the 4K experience made it a great experience. It was definitely a great movie and most see.

Like every Star Wars movie, there were inconsistencies and bad dialogue.  But this is Star Wars, and we take it for what it is.  Great ending to the story, and definitely made up for the last movie.   Satisfying and nostalgic.  Thanks JJ!

The Rise of Skywalker. I didn't hate it, wouldn't say I liked it. It had it's moments that I appreciated. It might be the best we could have gotten after The Last Jedi. Disney did a terrible job passing the torch.

A decent way to end the sequel Trilogy. But not a fitting end to the Skywalker saga. Was a jam packed film, that seemed to be trying to do fan service rather than tell a story. 
A good film, but not the best Star Wars film
Fantastic. Fixed the things I hated about TLJ, but built on the stuff I liked. A good end to the Skywalker saga. Definitely going to see it again.

While some critics complain about its fast-paced plot and unexplained events, we must all remember what this whole saga is really about. This movie did the best that it could have done given the status of the previous two movies, and it delivered a satisfying and emotional end to the trilogy.
